Revision history for Neo4j::Types

1.14  UNRELEASED

 - Define scalar context for list methods to yield number of elements
 - Define properties() to behave the same in list context as in scalar context.
 - Define result of reading a non-existent property to be undef.
 - Clarify that labels() and properties() must not return undef.
 - Recommend that users don't inherit type implementations from these modules.
 - Add Neo4j::Types::Generic namespace for generic type implementations.
 - Move spatial point implementation into Neo4j::Types::Generic namespace.
 - Add DateTime and Duration temporal types.
 - Fix loading of DateTime and Duration with "use Neo4j::Types".
 - Define methods and behaviour for the Neo4j 5 element ID.
 - Raise minimum required version of Perl to v5.10.1.
 - Add ByteArray type.
 - Specify the boolean values to be used (core bools on v5.36+).
 - Automatically register the custom warning category when it might be needed.
 - Avoid the term "role" in the documentation.
 - Include Test::Neo4j::Types 0.08 in this distribution.

1.00  2021-01-18

 - initial release, based on Neo4j::Driver 0.20 and Neo4j::Bolt 0.4200
